text.section:
As used in this section:
"Appurtenances" means the following devices that do not extend beyond the maximum vehicle width as established in subsection (2) of this section by more than six (6) inches on either side of a recreational vehicle:
Hand holds for entry or egress;
Load-induced tire bulge;
Rearview mirrors;
Splash and spray suppressant devices;
Turn signal lamps; and
Shade awnings and their mounting hardware;
"Recreational vehicle" has the meaning set forth in KRS 186.650(4); and
"Width exclusion safety devices" means the following devices that do not extend beyond the maximum vehicle width as established in subsection (2) of this section by more than three (3) inches on either side of a recreational vehicle:
Corner caps;
Lift pads;
Rear or side door hinges and protective hardware;
Rain gutters;
Side marker lamps;
Tarps and tarp hardware; and
Wall variations from a true flat.
